

A. DDL (Data Definition Language) Questions
1. Write an SQL query to create a table named Students with fields: StudentID, Name,
Age, Class, Marks.
2. Write a query to add a new column Email to the Students table.
3. Write a query to modify the Marks column to DECIMAL(5,2).
4. Write a query to drop the Email column from Students table.
5. Write a query to delete the entire Students table.
6. Write an SQL query to create a table Departments with DepartmentID (PK) and
DepartmentName.
7. Write a query to rename the table Students to StudentDetails.
8. Write a query to truncate all records from the Students table.

B. DML (Data Manipulation Language) Questions
1. Insert a new student record into Students (StudentID, Name, Age, Class, Marks).
2. Insert multiple records into the Students table using a single query.
3. Update the Marks of a student with StudentID = 10 to 95.
4. Increase all student Marks by 5 using an UPDATE query.
5. Delete a student record where StudentID = 5.
6. Delete all students who belong to Class &#39;10A&#39;.
7. Write a query to display all columns from the Students table.
8. Write a query to display only Name and Marks from the Students table.

C. WHERE Clause Questions
1. Write a query to find students whose Age is greater than 15.
2. Write a query to find students whose Marks are less than 40.
3. Select students where Class = &#39;10A&#39;.
4. Select students whose Marks are BETWEEN 60 and 80.
5. Find students with Age IN (14, 15, 16).
6. Display students where Name LIKE &#39;A%&#39;.
7. Find students where Marks IS NULL.
8. Find students where Age &gt;= 16 AND Marks &gt; 70.

D. Logical Operators (AND, OR, NOT) Questions
1. Find students who are in Class &#39;10A&#39; AND scored more than 75.

